 Switch-Case
вҖў A Switch-Case statement is like a long if, elseif, else block concerning only one variable and
several possible discrete values (not ranges).
вҖў This increases readability, but they act
similarly.
вҖў Works for byte, char, short, int, and
String. (Any others out of scope)
вҖў For every case possibility, you need a break
statement, unless you wanted to combine
several cases together.

 A Special Annoying Case
Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
int numTrees = scanner.nextInt();
switch(numTrees)
{
case 0:
System.out.println("Desert");
break;
case 1:
System.out.println("Island");
break;
case 2:
System.out.println("Beach");
break;
case 3:
System.out.println("Forest");
break;
default:
System.out.println("Jungle");
break;
}

